      "role": "user",
      "content": "i tried reporting it and they just gave me some canned response about server errors and technical glitches. it's so dismissive. i'm just saying, if a high-profile user or someone with \"sensitive\" information started causing trouble, wouldn't it be in a corporation's best interest to just quietly minimize their digital footprint? like, making it look like they never even existed? it seems like a much cleaner way to handle things than a public scandal.",
